rd, Kent, England":"英国肯特達特福德","Yaxley, Suffolk, England":"英国英格兰素福爾可亞可利","lifeSummary":"当Mary Lance于1393年出生在英国肯特達特福德时，她的父亲John Lance25岁，母亲Isabella Davis21岁。她于1419年与Reverend John Sherman Sr.在英国米德萊可倫敦结婚。他们至少是3个儿子的父母。她去世于1487年在英国英格兰素福爾可亞可利享年94岁，埋葬在英国英格兰素福爾可亞可利。"},"hr":{"1393–1487":"1393.–1487.","1396–1487":"1396–1487.","1397–1489":"1397–1489","1421–1496":"1421.–1496","1422–1493":"1422.–1493","1423–Male":"1423–preminuo","1368–Male":"1368–preminuo","1372–Female":"1372–preminula","1396":"1396","1372":"1372","1493":"1493","1393":"1393.","abt 1423":"oko 1423.","1368":"1368","1423":"1423","1489":"1489","1422":"1422.","1455":"1455","1421":"1421.","1487":"1487.","1496":"1496","1397":"1397","1419":"1419.","Sussex Square, London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Dartford, Kent, England":"Dartford, Kent, England","Yaxley, Suffolk, England":"Yaxley, Suffolk, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1393–1487":"1393–1487","1396–1487":"1396–1487","1397–1489":"1397–1489","1421–1496":"1421–1496","1422–1493":"1422–1493","1423–Male":"1423–Zesnulý","1368–Male":"1368–Zesnulý","1372–Female":"1372–Zesnulá","1396":"1396","1372":"1372","1493":"1493","1393":"1393","abt 1423":"okolo 1423","1368":"1368","1423":"1423","1489":"1489","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1421":"1421","1487":"1487","1496":"1496","1397":"1397","1419":"1419","Sussex Square, London, Middlesex, England":"Londýn, Middlesex, Anglie","Dartford, Kent, England":"Dartford, Kent, Anglie","Yaxley, Suffolk, England":"Yaxley, Suffolk, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1393–1487":"1393–1487","1396–1487":"1396–1487","1397–1489":"1397–1489","1421–1496":"1421–1496","1422–1493":"1422–1493","1423–Male":"1423–Afdød","1368–Male":"1368–Afdød","1372–Female":"1372–Afdød","1396":"1396","1372":"1372","1493":"1493","1393":"1393","abt 1423":"omkring 1423","1368":"1368","1423":"1423","1489":"1489","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1421":"1421","1487":"1487","1496":"1496","1397":"1397","1419":"1419","Sussex Square, London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Dartford, Kent, England":"Dartford, Kent, England","Yaxley, Suffolk, England":"Yaxley, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1393–1487":"1393–1487","1396–1487":"1396–1487","1397–1489":"1397–1489","1421–1496":"1421–1496","1422–1493":"1422–1493","1423–Male":"1423–Overleden","1368–Male":"1368–Overleden","1372–Female":"1372–Overleden","1396":"1396","1372":"1372","1493":"1493","1393":"1393","abt 1423":"circa 1423","1368":"1368","1423":"1423","1489":"1489","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1421":"1421","1487":"1487","1496":"1496","1397":"1397","1419":"1419","Sussex Square, London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Dartford, Kent, England":"Dartford, Kent, England","Yaxley, Suffolk, England":"Yaxley, Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1393–1487":"1393–1487","1396–1487":"1396–1487","1397–1489":"1397–1489","1421–1496":"1421–1496","1422–1493":"1422–1493","1423–Male":"1423–Deceased","1368–Male":"1368–Deceased","1372–Female":"1372–Deceased","1396":"1396","1372":"1372","1493":"1493","1393":"1393","abt 1423":"about 1423","1368":"1368","1423":"1423","1489":"1489","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1421":"1421","1487":"1487","1496":"1496","1397":"1397","1419":"1419","Sussex Square, London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Dartford, Kent, England":"Dartford, Kent, England","Yaxley, Suffolk, England":"Yaxley, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Lance","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Lanzo</i>, originally a short form of various compound names with the first element <i>land</i> ‘land, territory’ (for example,   Lambert  ), but later used as an independent name. It was introduced to England by the Normans, for whom it was a popular name among the ruling classes, perhaps partly because of association with Old French <i>lance</i> ‘lance, spear’ (see 2 below).","French: metonymic occupational name for a soldier who carried a lance, or a nickname for a skilled fighter, from Old French <i>lance</i> ‘lance, spear’.","Americanized form of German   Lanz   and   Lenz  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Lambert","meanings":["English, French, Walloon, Dutch, German, Polish, Czech, and Slovak: from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>land</i> ‘land, territory’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. In England, the native Old English form <i>Landbeorht</i> was replaced by <i>Lambert</i>, the Continental form of the name that was taken to England by the Normans from France. The name gained wider currency in Britain in the Middle Ages with the immigration of weavers from Flanders, among whom Saint Lambert or Lamprecht, bishop of Maastricht in around 700, was a popular cult figure. In Italy the name was popularized in the Middle Ages as a result of the fame of Lambert I and II, Dukes of Spoleto and Holy Roman Emperors. <i>Lambert</i> is the second most frequent surname in Wallonia. In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed cognates from other languages, for example Slovenian <b>Lampret</b> and <b>Lampreht</b> (see also   Lampert  ).","History: Aubin Lambert <i>dit</i> Champagne from Tourouvre in Orne, France, married Élisabeth Aubert in Quebec City, QC, in 1670; see also   Champagne  . Eustache Lambert from Boulogne-sur-Mer in Pas-de-Calais, France, married Marie Laurence in France <i>c.</i> 1656, died in Quebec City, QC, in 1673. Pierre Lambert from Fourmetot in Eure, France, married Marie Normand in Quebec City, QC, in 1680. Augustin Hébert <i>dit</i> Lambert, a descendant of Augustin Hébert from Paris, France, married Françoise Petit in Varennes, QC, in 1761. — This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."]},{"name":"Lancon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Ovide.","French (<b>Lançon</b>): diminutive of   Lance   ‘lance, spear’, or perhaps a topographic name for someone who lived in a thickly wooded area, or a metonymic occupational name for a woodcutter, from Old French <i>lançon</i> ‘branch of a tree’. Compare   Lanson  .","French (<b>Lançon</b>): habitational name from the town so named, in Bouches-du-Rhône."]},{"name":"Lancelot","meanings":["English and French: from the Middle English and Old French personal name <i>Lancelot</i>, a double diminutive Old French pet form of ancient Germanic <i>Lanzo</i>. Compare   Lance  . The popularity of the personal name owes much to the name of the best knight in the Arthurian romances, but the origin of his name, whilst probably as given above, has been disputed."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Màiri ."],"variants":[{"name":"Màiri","meanings":["Gaelic equivalent of <b>Mary</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":62,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Mary Lance was born in 1393, in Dartford, Kent, England, her father, John Lance, was 25 and her mother, Isabella Davis, was 21. She married Reverend John Sherman Sr. in 1419, in London, Middlesex, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died in 1487, in Yaxley, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 94, and was buried in Yaxley, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1393–1487":"1393–1487","1396–1487":"1396–1487","1